                  <div id="innerbodycontent" class="row nolayout"><div class="offset1 span10">
            <div id="sm-cog-elements" class="noprint"></div>
            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>Reference:HSK Standard Course 4上</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://amzn.to/2G1ZLgV"><img width="300" class="alignright link-amazon" src="https&#58;//images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/81wucel%2B2WL.jpg" /></a></span>
<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://amzn.to/2G1ZLgV">HSK Standard Course 4上</a>, by Liu Chang and Lu Jiang, contains 10 lessons. Authorized by Hanban, HSK Standard Course is developed under the joint efforts of Beijing Language and Culture University Press and Chinese Testing International (CTI). With HSK test papers as its primary source, HSK Standard Course is characterized by a humorous style, familiar topics and a scientific course design.
</p><p><b>HSK Standard Course 4上</b> is part 1 for this HSK level. Part 2 is <a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_4下" title="Reference:HSK Standard Course 4下">HSK Standard Course 4下</a>.
</p><p>You may also want to refer to our full list of <a href="HSK_4_grammar_points" title="HSK 4 grammar points">HSK 4 grammar points</a>.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_4上#Grammar_Points_by_Table_of_Contents"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Grammar Points by Table of Contents</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_4上#Grammar_Point_References_to_This_Book"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Grammar Point References to This Book</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_4上#HSK_Standard_Course_.28HSK_.E6.A0.87.E5.87.86.E6.95.99.E7.A8.8B.29"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">HSK Standard Course (HSK 标准教程)</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_Points_by_Table_of_Contents">Grammar Points by Table of Contents</span></h2>
<ol><li>Lesson 1: 简单的爱情 Simple love
<ol><li><a href="Many_types_of_&quot;not_only..._but_also...&quot;" title="Many types of &quot;not only... but also...&quot;">不仅 ......  也/还/而且 ......</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;never&quot;_with_&quot;conglai&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;never&quot; with &quot;conglai&quot;">从来</a>(see also <a href="Expressing_&quot;always&quot;_with_&quot;conglai&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;always&quot; with &quot;conglai&quot;">Expressing "always" with "conglai"</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;just&quot;_with_&quot;gang&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;just&quot; with &quot;gang&quot;">刚</a>(see also <a href="Comparing_&quot;gang&quot;_and_&quot;gangcai&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;gang&quot; and &quot;gangcai&quot;">Comparing "gang" and "gangcai"</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;even_if…&quot;_with_&quot;jishi&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;even if…&quot; with &quot;jishi&quot;">即使 ...... 也 ......</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_location_with_&quot;zai..._shang_/_xia_/_li&quot;" title="Expressing location with &quot;zai... shang / xia / li&quot;">(在) ...... 上</a>(see also <a href="Idiomatic_phrases_with_&quot;zai&quot;" title="Idiomatic phrases with &quot;zai&quot;">Idiomatic phrases with "zai"</a>)</li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 2: 真正的朋友 A true friend
<ol><li><a href="Coincidence_with_&quot;zhenghao&quot;" title="Coincidence with &quot;zhenghao&quot;">正好</a></li>
<li><a href="Approximations_with_&quot;chabuduo&quot;" title="Approximations with &quot;chabuduo&quot;">差不多</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;although&quot;_with_&quot;jinguan&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;although&quot; with &quot;jinguan&quot;">尽管</a></li>
<li><a href="The_&quot;however&quot;_adverb_&quot;que&quot;" title="The &quot;however&quot; adverb &quot;que&quot;">却</a></li>
<li><a href="Using_&quot;er&quot;_to_explain_contrasting_ideas" title="Using &quot;er&quot; to explain contrasting ideas">而</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 3: 经理对我印象不错 I've made a good impression on the manager
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_&quot;quite&quot;_with_&quot;ting&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;quite&quot; with &quot;ting&quot;">挺</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;originally&quot;_with_&quot;benlai&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;originally&quot; with &quot;benlai&quot;">本来</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;in_addition&quot;_with_&quot;lingwai&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;in addition&quot; with &quot;lingwai&quot;">另外</a></li>
<li>首先 ...... 其次 ......</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;no_matter&quot;_with_&quot;buguan&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;no matter&quot; with &quot;buguan&quot;">不管</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 4: 不要太着急赚钱 Don't be anxious to make money
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_&quot;mistakenly_think_that&quot;_with_&quot;yiwei&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;mistakenly think that&quot; with &quot;yiwei&quot;">以为</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;all_along&quot;_with_&quot;yuanlai&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;all along&quot; with &quot;yuanlai&quot;">原来</a>(see also <a href="Comparing_&quot;benlai&quot;_and_&quot;yuanlai&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;benlai&quot; and &quot;yuanlai&quot;">Comparing "benlai" and "yuanlai"</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Emphasizing_a_negation_with_&quot;bing&quot;" title="Emphasizing a negation with &quot;bing&quot;">并</a></li>
<li>按照</li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;even&quot;_with_&quot;shenzhi&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;even&quot; with &quot;shenzhi&quot;">甚至</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 5: 只买对的, 不买贵的 Buy the right, not the expensive
<ol><li><a href="Comparing_&quot;kending&quot;_&quot;queding&quot;_and_“yiding&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;kending&quot; &quot;queding&quot; and “yiding&quot;">肯定</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;in_addition&quot;_with_&quot;zaishuo&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;in addition&quot; with &quot;zaishuo&quot;">再说（备注：教材上有“把事情留到以后考虑”的意思，但是在Grammar Wiki 里只有“in addition”的意思。</a></li>
<li>实际</li>
<li><a href="Phrases_using_&quot;laishuo&quot;" title="Phrases using &quot;laishuo&quot;">对 ...... 来说</a></li>
<li>尤其</li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 6: 一份钱一分货 The higher the price, the better the quality
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_the_unexpected_with_&quot;jingran&quot;" title="Expressing the unexpected with &quot;jingran&quot;">竟然</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;multiples&quot;_with_&quot;bei&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;multiples&quot; with &quot;bei&quot;">倍</a></li>
